The Nigerian Government has confirmed five more cases of Coronavirus in the country. This brings the total number of cases in the country to eight. Minister of Health, Osagie Ehanire, made the disclosure at a press briefing in Abuja on Wednesday. A detailed travel history of each case is being compiled & contact tracing has begunOur National Emergency Operations Centre is supporting response in the statesThe Federal Government through @Fmohnigeria is conducting risk assessment to initiate other relevant measures pic.twitter.com/BuzK5JSKnD  More to come...